com.interpss.dstab

Interface BaseDStabNetwork<TBus extends BaseDStabBus<? extends DStabGen,? extends DStabLoad>,TBra extends DStabBranch>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    BaseAclfNetwork<TBus,TBra>, BaseAcscNetwork<TBus,TBra>, com.hazelcast.nio.serialization.DataSerializable, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, IAclfAreaZone, IAclfNetAdjustment, IAclfNetElement, IAclfNetFormMatrix, IAclfNetFunc, IAdaptable, IMultiNet, INet3WXfrElement, INetBranchElement<TBus,TBra>, INetBusElement<TBus>, INetworkElement, NameTag, Network<TBus,TBra>, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    DStab3PNetwork, DStabilityNetwork, Dynamic3PNetwork
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BaseDStabNetworkImpl, DStabilityNetworkImpl, Dynamic3PNetworkImpl

    public interface BaseDStabNetwork<TBus extends BaseDStabBus<? extends DStabGen,? extends DStabLoad>,TBra extends DStabBranch>
extends BaseAcscNetwork<TBus,TBra>
    A representation of the model object 'DStability Network'. Network container for all machine and controller elements for the stability simulation. There are two key concepts 1) discreate event and 2) continuous adjustment.
    1) event - discreate bus/branch event, such as fault. It results in some change to bus/branch parameters. Events are contained by the net object and referenced by Bus/Branch
    2) device - bus/branch dynamic device continously change system state by injecting current into the system. They are contained by the bus/branch object

    The following features are supported:

    • DStab Net Initialized
    • Allow Gen Without Mach
    • YMatrix
    • YMatrix Dirty
    • Static Load Model
    • Static Load Switch Volt
    • Static Load Switch Dead Zone
    • Net Eqn Iteration No Event
    • Net Eqn Iteration With Event
    • Saturated Machine Parameter
    • Net Change Listener
    • Dynamic Event List
    See Also:
    DstabPackage.getBaseDStabNetwork()
